LIberecké Automobilové Závody Logo LIAZ is a defunct Czech and Czechoslovak manufacturer of trucks. The company was formed in 1951 by the government as a division of Škoda, incorporating eight other truck manufacturers into a single conglomerate. In 1953 LIAZ became independent of Škoda, but still continued to use its name until 1984. After the 1989 revolution, there was however a significant loss of production. Source

Zetor Logo
Zetor is a brand of tractors, trademark and Czech manufacturer based in Brno, Líšeň. Since June 29, 2002, the only shareholder is a Slovak Company HTC Holding. The company manufactures farming tractors and tractor components. Zetor is the world’s first manufacturer to develop and launch production of tractor safety cabins. In the 70-year-long history, Zetor has sold over 1.3 million tractors. Currently, Zetor portfolio includes six model ranges with power from 40 to 160 hp.

Fischer Air Logo
air FISCHER, previously Fischer Air, was an airline headquartered in Prague, Czech Republic. It operated charter services for tour operator Fischer to over 30 destinations in Europe and Africa, as well as charter flights for other clients. Its main base was Ruzyně International Airport, Prague. In 2005 it was rebranded as Charter Air. Charter Air was not a success since a month later it was bankrupt. In October 2018 it announced its restart as “air FISCHER” as of April 2019.
You can download theFischer Airlogo on full-version of the page.
